notes: This recipe makes a thicker cornmeal cake, if baked in the same size (9-inch) cake pan as the recipe above. It yields approximately 2-1/2 cups of batter. If you make cornmeal muffins, use 1/4 cup of batter per cup for 10 muffins.
directions:
Sift the dry ingredients together into a bowl, then add in the rest of the ingredients. Mix well and pour into a greased cake or pie pan. 

Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°F.
name: Grandma Chatfield’s Cornbread
ingredients:
1 cup yellow corn meal
1 cup flour
1/4 cup white sugar
4 teaspoons baking POWDER
3/4 teaspoon salt
2 eggs
1 cup milk
1/4 cup Crisco or other soft shortening
